"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/0edd466e?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f9=
8315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0; text-decorati=
on: underline;" target=3D"_blank">recently credited</a> the company=E2=80=
=99s <a href=3D"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/9941d43c?m=3Db503a08a-c4=
e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0=
; text-decoration: underline;" target=3D"_blank">2024</a> acquisition of Vi=
zio for the =E2=80=9Ctriple-digit growth in advertising,=E2=80=9Dwhich rake=
d in roughly $6.4 billion in profit in 2025 and now represents <a href=3D"h=
ttps://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/8205b288?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f983=
15f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0; text-decoration=
: underline;" target=3D"_blank">roughly a fifth</a> of the company=E2=80=99=
s operating income.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6; c=
olor: #15212A;">Requiring new Vizio TV owners to log in with their Walmart =
account shows the company plans to take its surveillance even further. Its =
<a href=3D"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/5cff8a71?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4b=
fd-bc68-f98315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0; tex=
t-decoration: underline;" target=3D"_blank">stated goal</a> of this integra=
tion is to remove the disconnect between =E2=80=9Ccommerce and measurement=
=E2=80=9D and create an =E2=80=9Cidentity framework across devices, connect=
ing streaming engagement directly with retail interaction.=E2=80=9D</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #15212A;">In other wo=
rds, simply tracking what you=E2=80=99re watching and serving you targeted =
ads isn=E2=80=99t enough. Walmart wants to use that information to create a=
n endless feedback loop that enables you to buy, buy, buy. And Walmart is n=
ot alone=E2=80=94<a href=3D"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/29c641d6?m=
=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; =
color: #1dfdc0; text-decoration: underline;" target=3D"_blank">competitors<=
/a> are <a href=3D"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/9379e64d?m=3Db503a08a=
-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f98315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1df=
dc0; text-decoration: underline;" target=3D"_blank">integrati</a><a href=3D=
"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/bf3f08f3?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-bc68-f9=
8315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0; text-decorati=
on: underline;" target=3D"_blank">ng</a> advertising and e-commerce by <a h=
ref=3D"https://fulu-foundation.ghost.io/r/86f6e45b?m=3Db503a08a-c4e6-4bfd-b=
c68-f98315f6032b" style=3D"overflow-wrap: anywhere; color: #1dfdc0; text-de=
coration: underline;" target=3D"_blank">partnering</a> with Amazon to more =
precisely track and target audiences.</p><h2 id=3D"why-can-manufacturers-pe=
ep-on-the-device-you-own" style=3D"margin-top: 0; font-family: -apple-syste=
m, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1=
.11; font-weight: 700; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; margin: 1.5em 0 =
0.5em 0; font-size: 32px; color: #15212A;">Why can manufacturers peep on th=
e device you own?</h2><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6; co=
lor: #15212A;">Americans might not think twice about signing into an additi=
onal account when they set up a new TV. But if your neighbor stood outside =
your window while you watched <em>Friends</em>, you would probably close yo=
ur curtains and lock your door. If he showed up the next day to try to sell=
 you a Central Perk mug, you might look into getting a restraining order.</=
p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #15212A;">While=
 you can=E2=80=99t see them, what TV manufacturers and their ACR partners a=
re doing with your data is just as creepy. Once your TV is connected to the=
 internet, Amazon or Walmart might as well be sitting on your couch.</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 0 0 1.5em 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #15212A;">Today=E2=
=80=99s decline of ownership isn=E2=80=99t just about media=E2=80=94it=E2=
=80=99s now also about the device its consumed on. Invasive data collection=
 practices exploit consumers=E2=80=99 personal data while overly broad term=
s of service and anti-consumer design make it difficult to stop its flow. W=
ithout the ability to strip such technology out of the devices they own, co=
nsumers are faced with a double edged sword: protect their privacy, or use =
the smart features they paid for.</p>
